You’re going to have to work on your nutrition. You’re going to have to exercise. It’s requires breaking old habits which can be uncomfortable at first but once you adjust you’ll wonder why you didn’t start sooner.

All the best things take time

Growing up I was a ballerina. That part of me is still second nature because of of all the time put into that skill. That’s a skill that requires years of dedication, pain, blood, sweat and tears to perfect but for the ballerina, it’s a price they pay without hesitation. They put in the hours, days, years without rushing it. They understand that this is the process. 

My fitness journey has been the same experience. I’ve learned it can’t be rushed. We have to put in the years to fully develop a lifestyle out of it so that it becomes second nature. Just part of who we are.

Whatever your goals are, no matter how far out of reach they seem or how long it may take. You can get there if you are willing to put in the time and effort. 

If you don’t, you’ll have to watch others around you work towards and live YOUR dreams.

I know for certain that won’t be me.

I’m going after all the good things that take time💕

We chose this lil Bean and the rest is history. 

I have lots of plans for this girl. She is going to a board and train in a couple weeks to get service trained so that she can start to travel, attend events and go everywhere my boys and I go. 

Bean is the best buddy for my boys and I. They use her as a pillow, wrestle with her and she is so patient and tolerant and her breed mix makes her the perfect outdoors buddy❤️

This is EASILY a family favorite in my house! It’s so quick to make and the whole house enjoys them before we are out the door for the day. Healthy, yummy, easy! That’s what I’m talkin about 👌 

Ingredients:
 Ham or Turkey slices
Raw eggs
Turkey bacon
Shredded cheese
Salt & pepper
Crushed red pepper flakes 

Instructions:
Lay ham or Turkey slices over the top of each muffin hole. Cut Turkey slice in half and make an x shape on top of the Turkey slices. Gently push the Turkey slice and Turkey bacon down into the muffin tin. Crack one egg into each space. Top with shedded cheese and red pepper flakes, salt & pepper. Bake at 450 for 12-14 min. ENJOY!😊

Here are my personal guidelines I stick to when eating out. Whether it’s on vacation like this breakfast Buffet or just out with friends on the weekend, it is possible to enjoy a meal out while staying on track with your fitness goals. Here are my 3 guidelines 👇 

1. Prioritize protein- Choose from the leaner protein options. This means pretty much any meat and also cottage cheese and Greek yogurt if you’re eating breakfast like I did here. Avoid deep fried and battered proteins as these will have lots of carbs and fats along with them

2. Second option is always either fruits and or vegetables 👍 🍓 

3. 1 side of carbs. It’s easy to choose multiple sides of carbs but by sticking to just of the options you will be less likely to over consume them.

We can enjoy eating out and still working towards better health. It’s all about making better choices🫶🏼

2 of the most valuable mindset lessons that I believe have played a big role in transforming my life into what seemed nearly impossible years ago.

Our thoughts are the architects of our destiny. The mind is more powerful than we will ever know. My life started shifting when I started doing these 2 things. Not overnight. But over time.

I challenge you to start practicing these 2 things daily. 

1. Gratitude- What I’ve learned from practicing gratitude over the years is that giving thanks for what you want produces more of it, while thinking and complaining about what you don’t want produces more of that. You have to start small in the beginning because that’s when we are likely in a place where it’s hard to find the good. The very act of choosing to acknowledge even one good thing will help your gratitude. Find more and more daily to be grateful for. Truly grateful. A heart full of gratitude is a magnet for miracles.

2. Act “as if” technique for manifesting your dreams.- I know it sounds like hocus pocus to some but this is actually quite logical when it’s done right. The first step is to take a few minutes to get clear on what you want to achieve. Really picture it. How it feels and looks in a day of that life. Next step is to start to embody the energy, traits and daily actions of that future self. You want to be fit? Okay, really see that version of yourself. How do they walk, talk and act? They probably walk with a smile and confidence with their chin held high. They probably start their day with a certain routine and so on. This is your cue, embody that now, today. Live, talk, do the things that person would do. By acting as if what you are really doing is bringing yourself closer and closer to that reality with every aligning action.

What is one mindset technique that has helped you transform your life?

Quick & Easy Pumpkin Peanut Butter chocolate chip cookies 🍪 Fit girl version!

Because I cannot get enough of the pumpkin, peanut butter combo lately🎃 

Save this quick and easy recipe next time you need a sweet treat! Be sure to grab this PSL protein powder from my bio right now before it’s gone for the season. 

Ingredients:
•1 scoop pumpkin spice latte level-1 protein (🔗 in bio)
•1|2 cup peanut butter-creamy
•1/2 cup pumpkin puree
•1/4 cup sugar free maple syrup
•1 teaspoon almond extract
•1/4 teaspoon sea salt
•1/4 cup mini chocolate chips

Directions:
Preheat oven to 350 F. While the oven is heating, place a baking sheet for the cookies in the oven.

Add all ingredients to a bowl and Mix until smooth.

Remove the baking sheet from the oven and line with parchment paper. Place 2-3 tablespoons full of batter onto a preheated baking sheet.

Bake at 350 F for 12-15 minutes until edges are slightly brown.

Remove from the oven and the allow cookies to cool 5 minutes on baking sheet. They will continue cooking for those 5 minutes
.
Enjoy!

I struggled with lack of confidence and feeling unhappy. I was caretaker to my kids and others but I wasn’t caring for myself. Every ounce of my time was spread out with work and mom duties but at the end of each day I was so unhappy with myself. I didn’t feel confident or happy about my appearance and I definitely struggled with depression. 

Some of you may not know this but I was 50 lbs overweight years ago. At my heaviest I weighed 198lbs. 

I woke up one day, looked in the mirror and said “ENOUGH, I’m going to start caring for MYSELF too.” 

And so I did. 

I left an unhealthy relationship and started on my journey towards prioritizing ME, my health, my dreams, my vision for my life. 

And you know what…

Turns out taking better care of ME also makes me a better mom. I’m happier and healthier and can show them how to properly care for THEMSELVES as well. 

I’m more patient, have more energy and all around I’m a better me, for THEM.

If you are a mom or dad and find yourself caring for everyone but YOU and you feel unhealthy, unhappy and lack confidence, I encourage you to start prioritizing your fitness & nutrition. 

It’s the ticket that helped me fill my own cup and regain my happiness and confidence and I know I’m a better mom because I care for me too. 

At first it seems like time is a big obstacle for cooking healthier meals and working out. I promise you figure it out over time and it becomes easier to fit into your busy life. You start to love that time for your health and fitness and look forward to it. You can’t imagine your life any other way eventually and you’ll ask yourself 

Why didn’t I start sooner?!

The secret is to

MAKE IT FUN! I’ve never, ever forced it. In fact they ask to workout with me. But, It started with them from basically birth just watching me. Then they start to pick up the weights and do their own little dances and jigs lol

Next thing you know they are asking to come to the gym with you. When that happens I won’t get in my typical lift. Instead I follow them around and let them explore the equipment as they choose. This is how we raise a generation that won’t have fear or be timid to step into the gym as adults. 

Next thing you know (like in the case of my 14 yr old) you’re buying them their own gym membership and they are off on their own 🥹

🍓STRAWBERRY SHORTCAKE CUPCAKES

I’ve had the biggest sweet tooth craving for strawberry cake of some sort. So I whipped up these protein cupcake, bad boys.

I made the big cupcakes this time but actually prefer the normal sized cupcakes with this recipe so here’s how to make them

Super easy, super yummy with simple ingredients. Here’s the recipe🧁 Try Um out and tag me in your creation.

Ingredients:
•1/2 banana
•1 egg white
•7 large strawberries
•1 scoop @1stphorm strawberry milkshake level-1 protein(this is what makes the cakes taste so strawberry-licious)
•1/2 cup white cake mix
• whipping cream

Instructions:
Heat oven to 350 degrees F. In a blender, blend all the fresh strawberries into liquid jam. Set aside 1/4 cup of blended strawberries and put the rest into the fridge for later. In a bowl mash the banana until it’s a pasty consistency. Add the 1/4 cup blended fresh strawberries, egg white, white cake mix and 1 scoop strawberry milkshake level-1 protein. Mix all ingredients together well. Place six baking cups into a muffin tin. Pour cupcake mix evenly throughout the six baking cups. Bake for 12-15 min. Do not over cook. When the muffins are done remove from pan and let them cool completely. When they are cooled remove the freshly blended strawberries from the fridge. Top a good size dollop onto each muffin. Do not spread. Then top each muffin with another good size dollop of whipping cream. Voilà! Eat 1 or ALL!! Makes 6 cupcakes

Macros per cupcake (without whip cream)
Calories- 71
Carbs- 11g
Protein- 5g
Fat- >1g

If I could pick 1 word that is the ticket to getting results it would be COMMITMENT.

Getting in shape and staying in shape doesn’t mean you’re going to execute perfectly every single day. 

Too often I watch people start out on their new journey towards weight loss and then when things get tough and they struggle or don’t see progress quick enough they abandon ship and quit.

Commitment is choosing to keep going even though you’ve struggled. Even though you aren’t perfect at it, even though progress might be slow.

Healthy, Cinnamon Apple Crumble muffins 

These muffins are insanely good and also FILLING! I like to bake a batch and then eat one for breakfast with my coffee that week. Store them in the fridge and reheat for a few seconds then spread some butter in the center! Omg 😛 you’ll be addicted. Here’s the simple recipe

Ingredients for muffins:
•2 cups whole grain whole wheat flour
•1 scoop @1stphorm cinnamon cookie batter level-1 protein powder 
•4 tsp baking powder 
•1/2 tbsp ground cinnamon 
•1/2 tsp salt 
•1 cup unsweetened vanilla almond milk
•1/2 cup unsweetened apple sauce
•1/2 of a green apple (cubed)
•1/3 cup brown sugar

For protein icing:
•1/2 tbsp powdered sugar 
•1 tbsp unsweetened vanilla almond milk
•2 tbsp cinnamon cookie batter level-1 protein 

Directions:
Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Spray 6 count muffin tin with non stick spray. Wash, peel and cube green apple. Set aside brown sugar. Mix all ingredients for muffins in a bowl and then evenly distribute mix into the 6 count muffin tin. Next evenly sprinkle brown sugar on top of each muffin before baking. Bake for 18-21 minutes. While muffins are baking mix all ingredients for icing in a small cup or dish. Pour icing over fully cooked muffins. Muffins can be stored in a sealed container in the fridge for up to 5 days. Reheat In microwave or eat cold! Enjoy!

Protein 10g
Carbs 40g
Fat 1g

Join me as I reveal the 4 key elements you need to track for successful weight loss. Let’s get started!

1. Tracking total daily calories. This one is pretty obvious and well known. To lose weight we must consume less calories than we use through the day.

2.Tracking protein! This one is a big deal! Calories will control whether the scale goes up or down. But PROTEIN will determine whether we develop that lean and toned look or not. The scale can be going down but losing muscle mass could be why if we aren’t eating enough protein🤦‍♀️ I know you don’t want that. So eat up that protein.

3. We must be hydrated and getting in enough water. I hope I don’t need to explain this one. Aim for 100oz- a gallon per day!

4. GET ACTIVE! We need to have an exercise plan! It can be home workouts or gym workouts! Doesn’t matter. But get a plan from an expert and follow it.

In the beginning I was just trying to “eat healthier” but I learned “healthy” doesn’t clarify enough for a lot of people who are new to understanding nutrition. What one person might consider healthy will be different from the next and neither will equal results if those people don’t know how to balance out 3 things!
.
Those 3 things are PROTEIN, CARBS AND FATS:)
.
My biggest advise to really nail down this weight loss thing is to learn to count your macros because then you have a really good understanding of food and can make better decisions that will actually equal results!
.
Counting macros is a pretty simple concept, easy to learn, is extremely eye opening and it will allow you to eat more flexibly, enjoy the foods you love without harsh restrictions AND STILL LOSE WEIGHT! 🤗
.
I won’t get into teaching you how to count your macros in this post but you can do it the same way I did.
